<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911121-0174</DOCNO><DOCID>911121-0174.</DOCID><HL>   Cleveland-Cliffs Rights Plan</HL><DATE>11/21/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE C10</SO><CO>   CLF</CO><MS>BASIC MATERIALS (BSC)</MS><IN>DIVERSIFIED MINING (MNG)</IN><NS>SHAREHOLDER RIGHTS PLANS (SRP)</NS><RE>NORTH AMERICA (NME)OHIO (OH)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   CLEVELAND -- Cleveland-Cliffs Inc. said it changed itsshareholder rights plan to deter any takeover offers, addingthat it isn't aware of any current plans.   Under an amendment, if a group or person acquires 20% ofthe company's common stock, holders of the remaining rightswould be able to buy the company's common at a substantialdiscount -- each right would entitle holders to $170 ofcommon, up from $80 of common previously.</LP><TEXT>   Cleveland-Cliffs manages six iron ore mines in the U.S.and Australia.</TEXT></DOC>